Quick & Dirty collection of shell and PHP scripts
to fetch and parse version change log entries 
from the MySQL online manual into a local database
and to produce new changelog documents that can
span multiple versions ... (work in progress ...)

fetch-html.sh:

  shell script that fetches changelog
  pages for all MySQL main line releases
  starting with 5.0


schema.sql:

  database schema for storing change log 
  information


parse-changelogs.php:

  PHP script that parses the fetched change
  log files to extract individual change
  items and to fetch related bug information


generate-changelog.php

  Example script that fetches aggregated
  changes from MySQL 5.5.20 to 5.5.30
  and creates a simple HTML list of all
  changes between those two versions

